definition.value: An aromatic ketone that is 3,3-dimethylbutan-2-one in which the methyl groups at positions 1 and 4 are replaced by pyridin-3-yl groups. A steroid 11beta-monooxygenase (EC 1.14.15.4) inhibitor, it is used in the diagnosis of adrenal insufficiency.
A menaquinone whose side-chain contains seven isoprene units in an all-trans-configutation.
A tetracosenoic acid having a cis-double bond at position 15.
An N-acetyl-D-glucosamine that has alpha-configuration at the anomeric centre.

A member of the class of furonaphthodioxoles that is (5R,5aR,8aR)-5,8,8a,9-tetrahydro-2H-furo[3',4':6,7]naphtho[2,3-d][1,3]dioxol-6(5aH)-one substituted at position 5 by a 3,4,5-trimethoxyphenyl group.

An alkanesulfonic acid that is cyclohexanamine in which one of the amino hydrogens is substituted by a 2-sulfoethyl group. It is used as a buffer (pH range of 8.6-10.0) for studying pH-dependent processes in enzymology.
A hydroxyphenylalanine that is L-phenylalanine with a substituent hydroxy group at position 3.
A phenylalkylamine that is benzene in which one of the hydrogens is substituted by a 3-aminopentyl group.
A nucleotide in which the ribose moiety has one or more of its hydroxy groups substituted by hydrogen.
An amino disaccharide consisting of beta-D-Galp joined by a (1->4) glycosidic bond to 2-acetamido-2-deoxy-alpha-D-glucopranose.
An N-acyl-L-alpha-amino acid anion resulting from deprotonation of both carboxy groups of N-acetyl-L-glutamic acid.
A Good's buffer substance, pKa = 7.5 at 20 degreeC.

A semicarbazone resulting from the formal condensation of semicarbazide with 5-nitrofuraldehyde. A broad spectrum antibacterial drug, although with little activity against Pseudomonas species, it is used as a local application for burns, ulcers, wounds and skin infections.
An optically active form of 2-(hydroxymethyl)piperidine-3,4,5-triol having 2R,3R,4R,5S-configuration.

Propylphosphonic acid in which one of the hydrogens at position 3 is substituted by a formyl(hydroxy)amino group. An antibiotic obtained from Streptomyces lavendulae, it specifically inhibits DXP reductoisomerase (EC 1.1.1.267), a key enzyme in the non-mevalonate pathway of isoprenoid biosynthesis.
